## NanoPlot
reads=
sample=
threads=
outdir=
output= 


NanoPlot --threads $threads --prefix $sample --tsv_stats --outdir $outdir --loglength --color blue --format jpeg --plots kde dot --legacy hex --title $sample --fastq $reads

```
Copy these to local computer and view. The -report file has all information summarized. 

## FiltLong
```{bash}
sample=
min=1000
keep=90
input=
outdir=
output=$outdir/$sample.PC_FL.fastq

test -d $outdir || mkdir -p $outdir

filtlong --min_length $min --keep_percent $keep $input >> $output
```
FiltLong can only be used to trim/split with an external reference. 


## Chopper
```{bash}
sample=
min=1000
phred=10
input=
outdir=
output=$outdir/$sample.PC_FL_CH.fastq

test -d $outdir || mkdir -p $outdir

chopper -q $phred -l $min -i $input >> $output

```
For quality score information: https://help.nanoporetech.com/en/articles/6629615-where-can-i-find-out-more-about-quality-scores

